(if we've arrived here then there is a fault executing one of the M-codes)
(first we need to determine the value of the fault code [parameter #31])
(then call the appropiate o-word procedure to clean up the fault)
o<mcode_fault> sub
(MSG, executing mcode_fault o-word procedure)
#<passed_fault_code> = #31
(DEBUG, passed fault code = #<passed_fault_code>)

(M36 fault)
o<200> sub
(debug, o<#31> called)
M5
M65 P#<_ini[MOTION_OUT]INCHING>
M65 P#<_ini[MOTION_OUT]SOL_20A>
M65 P#<_ini[MOTION_OUT]SOL_20B>
o<200> endsub

(M37 fault)
o<201> sub
(debug, o<#31> called)
M5
M65 P#<_ini[MOTION_OUT]INCHING>
M65 P#<_ini[MOTION_OUT]SOL_20A>
o<201> endsub

(M39 fault)
o<202> sub
(debug, o<#31> called)
M5
M65 P#<_ini[MOTION_OUT]INCHING>
M65 P#<_ini[MOTION_OUT]SOL_20B>
o<202> endsub


o<#31> call

o<mcode_fault> endsub
